description: From a former trade name, VariTyper, presumably from variable and typer.

entries.meaning: (printing, historical) A kind of advanced typewriter that could use various different typefaces.

verbs.description: varitype (third-person singular simple present varitypes, present participle varityping, simple past and past participle varityped)

entries.meaning: (printing, historical) To prepare printed material using a machine of this kind.
